    "body": "I used some simple test code.\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    println!(\"{}\", whoami::username());\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd built \r\n```\r\n->  rustc -vV\r\nrustc 1.76.0-nightly (2f8d81f9d 2023-11-21)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 2f8d81f9dbac6b8df982199f69da04a4c8357227\r\ncommit-date: 2023-11-21\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.76.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 17.0.5\r\n```\r\nThen run in containers\r\n```\r\n[root@1bb8feffdd70 tmp]# cat /etc/redhat-release\r\nAlmaLinux release 8.4 (Electric Cheetah)\r\n[root@1bb8feffdd70 tmp]# ./whoami-test\r\nroot\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n[root@2700a994346a tmp]# cat /etc/redhat-release\r\nRed Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 7.0 (Maipo)\r\n[root@2700a994346a tmp]# ./whoami-test\r\nroot\r\n```\r\nSo I'm not sure if it's an issue with the `whoami` crate.",
